abstract: >-
  pySSMF is a Python package to simulate electronic properties of strongly correlated
  electronic systems using the Slave-Spin Mean-Field (SSMF) method. It provides a
  user-friendly interface to perform SSMF calculations, making it accessible to a wide
  range of researchers in the field of condensed matter physics. 
